<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst-pr" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Initial Conditions</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Initial Conditions</text></para>
    </header>
    <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="15" styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-24px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:24px; tabstops:none; font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-24px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:24px; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The next step is to set the initial heads. &#160;The heads will vary uniformly from 1 on the left to 0 on the right. &#160;Select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Data|Edit Data Sets…</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;Select the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Initial_Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> data set (under Required|Hydrology). &#160;Note that the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Use PHAST-style interpolation for all cells</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> checkbox becomes enabled on the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">PHAST Interpolation</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab. &#160;Check this checkbox. &#160;Leave the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Interpolation direction</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> set to X. &#160;Set </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Distance 1</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Distance 2</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 0 and 12 respectively. &#160;Set </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Value 1</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 1 and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Value 2</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 0 (fig. 46).</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><image src="Ex1InitialHead.bmp" scale="75.00%" width="492" height="380" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 46.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Data Sets dialog box showing how to set up a gradient in initial head.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <list id="7" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="16" styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-24px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:24px; tabstops:none; font-family:&apos;Times New Roman&apos;; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:-24px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:24px; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The next step is to set the initial conditions for chemistry. &#160;The solution, surface and kinetics will all have an initial index of 1. With the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Data Sets</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box still visible, set the formula for </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Chemistry_Initial_Solution</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Chemistry_Initial_Surface</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Chemistry_Initial_Kinetics</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> each to 1. They are found under Required|Chemistry. Click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Apply</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and then the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Close</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> buttons.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
</topic>
